    <refnamediv>
        <refname>hirte-agent-config</refname>
        <refpurpose>Configuration file description for hirte-agent</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>

    <refsect1>
        <title>Description</title>

        <para>
            The basic file definition used to bootstrap hirte-agent.
        </para>
    </refsect1>

    <refsect1>
        <title>File format</title>

        <para>
            The hirte-agent configuration file is using the .ini file format.
        </para>

        <refsect2>
            <title>[Node]</title>

            <para>
                All fields to bootstrap the hirte-agent are contained in the [Node] group.
            </para>
            <para>
                The following keys can be present in this group:
            </para>
            <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><option>Name</option> (string)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>
                            The unique name of this agent.
                        </para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                    <term><option>Host</option> (string)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>
                            The host of the hirte manager to connect to. Must be a valid IPv4 or IPv6.
                        </para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                    <term><option>Port</option> (uint16_t)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>
                            The port of the hirte manager to connect to.
                        </para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
            </variablelist>
        </refsect2>

        <refsect2>
            <title>[Logging]</title>

            <para>
                Fields in the [Logging] group define the logging behavior of hirte-agent. These settings are overridden by the environment variables
                for logging.
            </para>
            <para>
                The following keys can be present in this group:
            </para>
            <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><option>Level</option> (string)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para> The level used for logging. Supported values are: </para>
                        <para>
                            <option>DEBUG</option>, <option>INFO</option>, <option>WARN</option>, <option>ERROR</option>
                        </para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                    <term><option>Target</option> (string)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para> The target where logs are written to. Supported values are: </para>
                        <para>
                            <option>stderr</option> , <option>journald</option>
                        </para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>

                <varlistentry>
                    <term><option>Quiet</option> (string)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para> If true, this flag prevents any logs to be written. </para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
            </variablelist>
        </refsect2>
    </refsect1>
    <refsect1>
        <title>Example</title>
        <programlisting>
[Node]
Name=agent-007
Host=127.0.0.1
Port=2020

[Logging]
Level=DEBUG
Target=journald
Quiet=false
        </programlisting>
    </refsect1>

